author: Code With Huw
description:
#byte #smalltalk #programming

When I first read this issue of Byte, I couldn’t make any sense of it. Computers used keyboards, so what was this strange “mouse” device? Computers showed text on a screen. So what were these windows and menus? The truth of the matter is that in August 1981, the computer software described in this magazine was far, far ahead of the software most of us had installed on our work or (relatively rare!) home computers.

Was this the most significant computer magazine ever published? In my view, I think it probably was…

Object Orientation (the influence of Smalltalk): playlist
https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PLZHx5heVfgEvuveKG1T7BBSuDOTHl1eLl


MORE VIDEOS
=============
I have hundreds of videos and even complete programming courses on my YouTube channel. They cover everything from low-level programming in C to coding an adventure game in C# or Java. I cover languages as varied as Ruby, Object Pascal and Smalltalk. No matter what your programming level
title: The 44 Year Old Computer Magazine That Changed Everything!
